docstring:
"""
        Return an encoded string of all query string arguments.

        `safe` specifies characters which don't require quoting, for example::

            >>> q = QueryDict(mutable=True)
            >>> q['next'] = '/a&b/'
            >>> q.urlencode()
            'next=%2Fa%26b%2F'
            >>> q.urlencode(safe='/')
            'next=/a%26b/'
        """
name: urlencode
